The feasibility in real samples was further explored by applying CD-LEuH@MnO2 to the detection of AA in water samples, milk as well as fruit juices. The recoveries were 92.7–116.0 % for the fluorescence detection system and 95.1–109.3 % for the UV colorimetric detection system, which were less than 3 % (Table 2
                        ). It shows that the designed sensing system has high applicability and accuracy in the detection of AA in real samples. When comparing the newly – constructed dual-mode sensing system in this paper with previously reported ones in the literature, it is evident that the system presented here features a low LOD (Table 3
                        ).
